evaluation.response:
It can be really hard to get out of your head, especially when you're feeling overwhelmed, anxious, or unsure about what to do next.

If you notice that you're spending more and more time on your phone, and it's starting to negatively impact other areas of your life, it might be helpful to take a step back and reevaluate your priorities. Here are some suggestions:

*   Set limits for yourself. Try using an app or tool that tracks how much time you're spending on your phone.&#x20;
*   Create healthy routines around your phone use, especially when you notice an increase in phone time.
*   Try to be more mindful of how you're using your phone, like noticing when you're reaching for it out of habit or boredom.

You could talk to a mental health professional. They can offer additional support and guidance, and help you develop healthy coping strategies.&#x20;
